I don't think it is woth it to respec between templates that are relatively close.<br>
<br>
All weapon types, since version 1.53, are more or less equal for a skald : slash is now a superior damage type, hammer still have the best styles, sword style sucks globally BUT if you have an end regen shaman buff, the brutal cost of polar rift is moot so swords (imho) takes the lead style-wise.<br>
I don't think it is worth it now (wasn't the case when hammer was &quot;uber&quot;) to respec from one weapon to another, all have advantages and drawbacks and are a question of taste.<br>
<br>
You only have one respec. According to Mythic track record and recent posts, you will not be entitled to another respec even if they do some meaningful changes to spec lines (like they didn't give respecs to paladins, thanes and shamans after last patch). My suggestion is to save your respec for further uses if Mythic decides to tweak game balance again. You will not see enough of a difference between your 2 templates to justify wasting your one and only respec. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mance>Mance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/31/02 4:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=379.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: As i have said previously</span><hr size=1> Go with higher weapon , parry is for sissies :P <p>&lt;center&gt;<br>
