<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I considered the following specs 50/43/2, 47/46/5, 46/46/10, and 44,46,17.<br>
<br>
I went with cookie cutter 44/46/17.  Why?  Well......  you can get decent (albeit subpar) defense through parry with 17 +items 11 +RR (up to 10 I believe) and MoParry (3% or 6 points/lvl).  Thats not bad.  Can potentially build parry up quite high.  Still you may not parry a whole lot in RvR with group modifiers, to hit bonus styles, etc but still one parry may save your life.  The point is debatable.  The main reason i went this template with 17 parry is that I like PvE.  I like looting for crafters (and me too) and helping guildies lvl.  parry helps me greatly in this role.  In my PvE gear and MoParry 1 I have 30 Parry (35 if I drop cha by 19points).  So I parry pretty well in PvE.  If i get some nice dex buffs I paary like mad.<br>
<br>
Thats MHO anyway.<br>
